  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p><em><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl10_LabelType\">You have put in many hours practicing with flashy alchemical items that enhance your Perform skill.</span></p></em>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Benefits</strong></p>\n<p><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl00_LabelType\"><span id=\"ctl00_MainContent_DataListTypes_ctl10_LabelType\">When you use an attention-getting alchemical item such as a flask of alchemist&rsquo;s fire, smokestick, thunderstone, or another appropriate alchemical item (GM&rsquo;s discretion) as part of a performance, you gain a +2 trait bonus on your Perform check for the duration of that performance. The item is expended without its normal effects and only serves to make your performance more impressive; for example, you could pretend to ignite yourself with alchemist&rsquo;s fire as part of a Perform (comedy) check or make a dramatic appearance with a smokestick as part of a Perform (act) check, but you would not actually take fire damage or gain concealment from smoke.</span><br /></span></p>",
